Standby is officially here! I wrote this song about finding the right person while being in the wrong relationship. It’s my lighthearted take on a delicate topic. This song is very special and personal to me, and it’s the first song off of my (ALBUM!!) that I wanted to share with the world. I hope you love it as much as I do. 

MASSIVE thank you @sethcookmusic for being the incredible force that you are. Seth wrote this song with me, produced it, played nearly everything, and mixed the track. I couldn’t appreciate you more for really taking your time with this music, and taking it to the place that you did. You are the most amazing collaborator and I am so grateful to have worked with you on this music. 

Thank you @thatsjusonbass for laying down your bass swag on this track. Collaborating with you is always a great time.

Thank you @ethan.barrette for engineering the drums on this track at @addictionsound -
You have an amazing ear. We had the best time working with you. 

Thank you @jeff.dickerhoof for mastering this track! I’ve been a fan of yours for a while, and am thrilled to have you on this.

Thank you @beacasso for experimenting with me on the photos for Standby. You’re a 💫 

Thank you @rhschaefer for helping me bring my vision for this artwork to life! I’ve been wanting to work with you for some time now, and it was the most enjoyable experience.

Lastly, thank YOU guys for the support you’ve already shown me through this. I can’t wait to hear what you think. 

Love,

Bri
🌞Everyone who put their love into Standby🌞 #credits #newmusic

he said he loved me more than ever as he built walls around his lonesome treasure.. 🌹”I’ve Never Loved” available everywhere December 29th. #newmusic

“I’ve Never Loved” is officially out everywhere. I wrote this song as I was falling in love for the first time. I don’t think it’s possible to live up to the depth of the feeling with words, but to me, this is what it sounds like. 
I hope when you hear this, it reminds you of a love you’ve felt. 

Thank you thank you thank you to the incredible team that helped me bring “I’ve Never Loved” to life. You are all so talented & I feel very lucky to have been apart of this with you. 

Photo by Marissa Blair (@mariss_bliss )
